Put the butter, sugar and oats in a saucepan and stir over a high heat for 4–5 minutes, or until toasted and crunchy. Set aside to cool.Measure the mascarpone and cream into a bowl and whisk until soft peaks form when the whisk is removed from the bowl.Add the whisky, 300g/10½oz raspberries and two-thirds of the cooled oats. Mix until combined, but try to keep the raspberries fairly whole.Spoon into glasses and top with the remaining raspberries and crunchy oats.